FT  16 APR 93 / World News in Brief: Srebrenica bombarded
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Serb artillery and infantry pounded the besieged town of Srebrenica and
radio hams reported that Moslem defenders had been driven back to within 1
1/4 miles of the town. Earlier a UN convoy left with only five elderly women
on board after local leaders blocked a mass refugee evacuation. Major and
Owen reject arms call, Page 2; PM pressed, Page 12; Bosnia waits, Page 16
