<HEADLINE>
FT  15 APR 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: Platinum prices up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Commodities Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The increasing tension in South African cities pushed platinum prices up in
both London and New York yesterday, writes Our Commodities Staff. In London
speculative buying and short covering took the price to more than Dollars
370 a troy ounce in late trading, the highest since early February. Nymex
July futures jumped Dollars 9.60 to Dollars 372 in early trading. 'The
market is a bit thin and small parcels can exaggerate price moves,' one
dealer said. South Africa supplies about 75 per cent of western world
platinum, which is used principally in jewellery, autocatalysts and
electronics.
</TEXT>
