FT  15 APR 93 / Shark tank scrapped
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RHODRI DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PLANS FOR a shark tank at London's Planet Hollywood restaurant have been
scrapped after architects found the fish too unreliable, Rhodri Davies
writes.
The theme restaurant (shown left in design and under construction) is due to
open in the West End on May 17. It will have exhibits from films Terminator
2 and Rocky and the handcuffs from 9 1/2 Weeks, but architects Blair
Eastwick abandoned plans for a live shark exhibit. Partner Michael Eastwick
said: 'Baby sharks cost a small fortune and you have no guarantee of an
extended lifetime with those fish.'
Diners will enter the James Bond room through a gun barrel.
