<HEADLINE>
FT  15 APR 93 / UK union pact with Teamsters
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's Transport and General Workers Union yesterday signed what it
called an historic agreement with the International Brotherhood of Teamsters
of the US, writes Robert Taylor.
The TGWU said the two unions would consult about developing a co-ordinated
approach toward the United Parcel Service company.
The co-operation agreement would also cover an exchange of information and
educational facilities but concentrate on developing common interests in
global transport.
'As capital becomes more internationally mobile, so must organisations of
labour co-ordinate their work across national boundaries', said Mr Bill
Morris, TGWU general secretary.
