<TEXT>
Sir, Samuel Brittan (Economic Viewpoint, April 8) is sympathetic to
Professor Patrick Minford's view that the equilibrium rate of unemployment
in the UK is 1m.
Does either Mr Brittan or Prof Minford have any idea when we might reach
that equilibrium? The other 2m would like to know.
John Edmonds,
general secretary,
